The `SMTPAppender` only evaluates the subject of an e-mail as a [pattern](https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/layouts.html#Patterns). The remaining fields are immutable.

What you can do is to use [`RoutingAppender`](https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/appenders.html#RoutingAppender) to create a different SMTP appender per e-mail recipient. Something like this should work (I didn&#39;t test it):

```lang-xml
&lt;Routing name=&quot;Routing&quot;&gt;
  &lt;Routes pattern=&quot;$${ctx:mailto}&quot;&gt;
	&lt;Route&gt;
         &lt;SMTP  name=&quot;WarningMail-${ctx:mailto}&quot; 
                subject=&quot;$${ctx:subject:-Int HealthCheck Warning}&quot;
                to=&quot;${ctx:mailto:-root@example.com}&quot; 
                from=&quot;support@company.com&quot;
                smtpHost=&quot;ldnsmtp&quot; 
                smtpPort=&quot;25&quot; 
                bufferSize=&quot;2000&quot; 
                ignoreExceptions=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
                &lt;ThresholdFilter level=&quot;info&quot; onMatch=&quot;ACCEPT&quot; onMismatch=&quot;DENY&quot;/&gt; 
                &lt;EmailLoggerLayout /&gt;               
         &lt;/SMTP&gt;
	&lt;/Route&gt;
  &lt;/Routes&gt;
  &lt;IdlePurgePolicy timeToLive=&quot;15&quot; timeUnit=&quot;minutes&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/Routing&gt;
```

