You can use `beanFactory` to get the configuration properties bean by its type.

```java
@Scheduled(fixedDelayString = 
            &quot;#{beanFactory.getBean(T(com.package.MyProperties)).reloadPeriod}&quot;)
public void doSomeRecurrentStuff() {
	// ...
}
```

Alternatively, implement [`SchedulingConfigurer`](https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/scheduling/annotation/SchedulingConfigurer.html) to programmatically set up scheduled tasks.

```java
import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;
import org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.SchedulingConfigurer;
import org.springframework.scheduling.config.ScheduledTaskRegistrar;

@Configuration
public class SchedulerConfig implements SchedulingConfigurer {
	@Autowired
	private MyProperties myProperties;
	
	void doSomeRecurrentStuff() {
		// some work
	}

    @Override
    public void configureTasks(ScheduledTaskRegistrar taskRegistrar) {
        taskRegistrar.addFixedDelayTask(this::doSomeRecurrentStuff, 
              myProperties.getReloadPeriod());
    }
}
```

